{
  "stem": "3952.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Although I started with two of my brothers together in the same cheder, and my brothers are-- one is three years and one is four years older than me-- but I was the one-- I was the kind of one who could remember a whole page of-- of Talmud by heart for every Shabbos and I used to get a piece of chocolate, which was a big thing for us.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We didn't see so much chocolate in the house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were happy to see bread.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very difficult to talk about happy memories.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- there-- there were not-- happy memories I really don't have.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, there were happy moments if I kicked a goal at soccer on the soccer game.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was very good, but happy memories per se as a child-- it is even difficult for me to-- to imagine myself as a child.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was never a child.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was so-- so serious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I can remember I started going to cheder when I was three years old.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they taught me to pray, to read the alphabet and to pray.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then I knew that, and I knew it very fast because I had a photographic memory.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I-- they gave me to learn the Torah, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Immediately I knew that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They started with [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Later, they started with [INAUDIBLE]. and I tell you by six-- I see boys today in America, by six they don't know what a [INAUDIBLE] is yet.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They don't even know what it is.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I already knew by heart pages, whole pages of [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So there wasn't time for-- for happy moments.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This is very difficult.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Yeah, happy moments, yes, maybe-- maybe, yes-- when I used to go Shabbos afternoon, we used to go to the [INAUDIBLE] of the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
